  "response": "Technically, white is not a true color but rather the presence of all colors or the reflection of all visible wavelengths of light. In visual perception:\n\n1. In physics, white light contains all wavelengths of the visible spectrum combined.\n\n2. In art and design, white is considered a color and is used as such.\n\n3. In color theory, white is considered an achromatic color (along with black and gray), meaning it lacks hue.\n\nSo the answer can depend on the context - scientifically, it's not a color in the traditional sense, but practically, it's often treated as a color.",
